  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QUANTITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<p>Quantity Surveyor (Architectural)</p><ul><li>Prepare tender submission, handle progress claims, variation orders and finalize project accounts</li><li>Administration of tenders - prepare Quotation, tender and contract documents including Bill of Quantities, cost estimation, cost control and budgeting</li><li>Final Account Preparations</li><li>Take-off quantity, prepare bill of quantity, cost estimation for tender & on-going projects</li><li>Monitor project delivery to ensure materials are in accordance to contractual terms and conditions</li><li>Updating & tracking of drawings to ensure timely information</li><li>Maintain proper & complete set of contract documents</li><li>Contracts administration such as valuations of variations etc.</li><li>Attend site meetings (if required) and assist supervisors in letter/report writing correspondences</li><li>Other adhoc duties assigned by Manager</li><li></li></ul><ul><li>Diploma in Quantity Surveying or equivalent</li><li>Possess minimum 1 year of working experience in local construction industry</li><li>Good interpersonal skills and communication skills with people of all levels</li><li>Preferred to be bilingual in English and Chinese (Need to liaise with Mandarin-speaking associates and colleagues)</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 1,
